<p>Rob Balder, creator of <a href="http://www.partiallyclips.com/"><em>PartiallyClips</em></a>, suggested that no matter how boring the flag of Virginia is, it is still cool because it featured a female human breast. (<a href="http://hwc.livejournal.com/51754.html">the discussion</a>)</p>
<p>Andrew Rogers suggests scrapping the original flag---which features the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Seal_of_Virginia">state seal</a> desiged by George Mason---for <a href="http://www.andrewrogers.net/Flags/new_state_flags.htm#Virginia_">something more geometrical</a>.</p>
<p>I still say you could jazz up the original design just a bit and make something very good:</p>
<p>Old flag:<br /><img src="http://halcanary.org/images/Flag_of_Virginia.jpg" alt="[flag]" width="291" height="200" /></p>
